<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-04T13:49:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-04T13:49:00-05:00" n="408" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1408</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Scholle</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-04T14:00:00-04:49">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1916, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Since the civil officials under the treaty have assumed office, does the
                            Department wish all Federal civil administrations now conducted by order
                            of the President turned over to the Haitian Government beginning October
                            first? Arrangements have been made with the Haitian Government for the
                            continuation of work by occupation till October first. Expeditionary
                            commander believes it necessary to retain control of hospitals, prisons,
                            and charities to insure proper maintenance.</p>
                        <p>On account of health of American troops, sanitation should be retained by
                            occupation until sanitary engineer is appointed and installed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Scholle</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>